From this latter point of view, all current technologies are not good enough for us; this gives more work to algorithm designers.
That is, we have to remember not only the resolution on the X and Y axes, but also in Z.
Also important is the speed, the number of frames per second.
Human movements are quite dynamic and current 30fps are really scarce, especially for gestures.
Steven Bathiche, from our laboratory in Redmond, made an adjustable processing delay contact sensor from 1 to 100 ms and it should be noted that the modern mass-produced sensors are closer to the second value (60-100).
