The hands feel nothing!
What answers does your group prepare for this challenge?
In my lectures I often say that augmented reality is the seventh breakthrough in the interaction between man and machine.
I think the eighth might well be the addition of tactile sensations.
Meanwhile, one of the most interesting tricks is the use of the second hand as a support for the image.
Record the touch perfectly!
But there are also technologies that are truly oriented to bring tangibility to these "in-air" images. For example, the interference of various ultrasonic rays directed to a specific point where the finger is located gives a feeling similar to that one feels if someone was blowing it in the fins of the fingers, but that feeling is still very weak.
There are also wrist bracelets that influence the nerve endings of the fingers, this also a promising direction.
- Have you tried to fool the brain?
