Šimon Ornest: At our concerts we want to accumulate positive energy
It is said that in just under a month the end of the world is coming, what do you think about it?
It’s just one of so many other alarming news we like to catch.
The music group The Tap Tap rather likes to joke about this and we like to say that we are the only music group in the world that manages to gather enough positive energy to postpone the end of the world or to avoid it.
Also, in December you are organizing a truly original project: three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you explain it to our readers?
This is a state-run act that we have been planning for two years.
We decided to take advantage of the marketing potential that has the end of the Mayan calendar set out for December 21 at 11:10 in the morning.
The day before, on 20 December at 9 p.m., we will organise 3 simultaneous concerts in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end approximately at the same time as the Mayan calendar ends on Kiribati Island, in the Pacific Ocean, 12 hours ahead of our time zone.
Who came up with this idea?
Initially it was my idea, then we were forging the project together with our designer Honza Augusta.
In addition to wanting to gather enough positive energy and avoid the end of the world, we also want to reflect, together with society, on the state in which we will leave the world to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar we have also created a unique collection of items: boots, t-shirts, bags and original keychains against the end of the world that can be purchased at www.e-tap.cz, another way to support us.
The group The Tap Tap, along with other performers, also sang the so-called anthem against the end of the world, which is titled “End of the world, cancelled.”
Currently it’s very popular on YouTube, can it be heard at charitable concerts?
Of course, and it will be just the last, well, as long as everything goes well and the world doesn't end...
All performers will sing it at the same time at all three concerts.
The anthems will be linked to each other simultaneously thanks to the special live broadcast on Czech Television.
Tomáš Hanák has written the lyrics of this song and plays the protagonist role of Jesus in the video clip, where Xindl X...
How did this collaboration emerge?
We work together even with other personalities from the Czech cultural scene, besides organizing many charitable events and concerts...
We make every effort to participate in this project.
It has been shown that most of them are interested and have fun working with us.
What will the money raised at the concerts against the end of the world be for?
Equipment for the Studeo educational centre without barriers, which we have completed in its sixth consecutive year with the civil association Tap in Jedličkův ústav.
Students of the Jedličkův ústav school regularly receive the visit of teachers with whom they perform fun and interesting activities.
Students do not have enough financial means to pay the teachers and we make an effort to make it possible.
As part of the completion of the works in Jedličkův ústav, there will be an independent building to which we will move with this project.
In each concert, several groups and performers perform.
What are the selection criteria?
We are trying to develop a programme that is attractive to all generations, including children.
For example, in Prague will perform Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý.
For more detailed information, please visit www.kpks.cz.
Are you planning on another similar "spectacular action" in the future?
In May we will perform for the first time at the Pražské jaro festival, so here we will surely prepare an attractive program with interesting guests.
Next year we would also like to play at the Bohemian National Hall in New York and I personally, taking advantage of being in the United States, would like to complete it with performances in Washington and Chicago.
Your plans abroad are not precisely minimalist, so far you have acted for example in Madrid, Brussels, London or Moscow.
The Tap Tap is a group of people with disabilities.
What is the logistics and organization of these trips?
It’s not as difficult as it may seem at first glance.
There are five members in electric wheelchairs, the chairs must travel in the luggage compartment and we also carry a lot of weight, the boxes with the instruments...
However, until now, we have managed well. ČSA and British Airways were perfectly prepared, which keeps me surprised.
Even in Moscow, where we have recently returned from, everything went smoothly.
Thanks to exits abroad you can compare the different attitudes of society towards the disabled and other aspects.
What have you encountered so far?
In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, everything works better than here; in Russia we have witnessed that, in the east, there is a long way to go.
Unlike Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there it is still uncommon for a person to travel alone through the city center in an electric wheelchair.
Something as common as it is, for example, giving preference to someone in a wheelchair in an elevator, there is not.
Fortunately, a civilian association has been created that strives to address the problems of people with disabilities.
In what aspects should we take the example of more advanced countries?
There are many aspects in which we go behind...
But it is important to mention that the improvement and improvement of the situation always depends on the people it directly affects.
In London and Madrid it is very normal for people with severe disabilities to travel on their own in public and can go to service, to the museum, wherever they want to go.
But it’s not very common for a large number of people with disabilities to actively participate in social life, in this respect, with The Tap Tap Let’s go a bit ahead!
A respectful or barrierless society is one thing, but when the time comes when eminent athletes, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers will begin to change everything.
So far, these are isolated cases of people who have great willpower.
The Tap Tap group is currently very popular, but if we look at a few years ago, what led you to form the group in 1998?
I entered Jedličkův Ústav as an educator, where there were a lot of young people around me who wanted to dedicate themselves to something.
And since I am a musician, I play, among others, the saxophone, I founded an amateur group with a coworker.
And over time, as our moderator Láďa Angelovič says, we got a bit off our hands (laughs).
However, popularity hasn’t come until recent years, or am I wrong?
It is true that it helped us a lot to connect with famous singers and also actively work to promote the group.
We come to the conclusion that the work that is not seen is as if it does not exist.
Thanks to the aid of the European Union, we can also afford teachers in quality, equipment, etc.
Did you intend to go so far with The Tap Tap?
From the beginning I saw the potential that there was, that something could be done otherwise.
The world of the show is full of things that resemble each other.
It is logical, in its own way, that everything new is accepted with caution and takes a long time to accept.
There are few extraordinary things, but I dare to say that The Tap Tap is one of them.
The impression of someone who sees us for the first time is clearly compassion, it is a natural reaction.
But compassion is totally superfluous because people with disabilities are not abandoned beings who suffer and of whom we should have compassion.
There are people who are able to live a full life and develop, on the condition, of course, that they have the necessary means.
I always say that if something goes well for people with disabilities, then it’s not just a breakthrough for them, but for the whole society.
Did the fact that you are a demanding boss help, as many people describe you?
If we want to do quality work, we have to be rigorous in many respects and demand some discipline.
I think it's completely normal.
Some people arrive with a romantic vision and head in the clouds and when they learn that they have to go to rehearsal for two days, go to the preparatory test and spend a lot of time traveling and in concerts, the initial euphoria quickly abandons them.
But that’s how it works everywhere, in every group that wants to work and get something.
The Tap Tap group currently has twenty members.
How many of them were already in the beginning of 1998?
Only one: Láďa Angelovič.
We are an open group, people come in and out, you can’t avoid it.
Whoever has will and desire will always find the doors open
